n on July 26 and finish on August 11.\", \"from\": 267, \"to\": 372, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 313, \"end\": 318, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Paris\", \"score\": 0.621119193468231, \"rank\": 0.6099969386169178, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His Majesty King Charles III is to become Patron of the British Olympic Association.\", \"from\": 374, \"to\": 458, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 391, \"end\": 402, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_III_of_Spain\", \"score\": 0.9914161570307755, \"rank\": 0.004785936187554634, \"text\": \"Charles III\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_III_of_Spain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_III_of_Spain\"}, {\"begin\": 430, \"end\": 457, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Olympic_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"British Olympic Association\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Olympic_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Olympic_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He takes over the Patronage from the late Queen Elizabeth II, who had been Patron of the BOA since her ascension to the throne in 1952.pic.twitter.com/VdFu86gZ59  - Team GB (@TeamGB)May 24, 2024  Sir Hugh Robertson, chair of the BOA, said: \\\"We are delighted that His Majesty The King has agreed to take on the patronage of the BOA.\", \"from\": 460, \"to\": 791, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 549, \"end\": 552, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Olympic_Association\", \"score\": 0.9999988451040583, \"rank\": 1.1548851646980942e-06, \"text\": \"BOA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Olympic_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brit